A very basic text 2 image Flux Dev workflow for understanding the basics of it.
A very basic text 2 image Flux Schnell Quantized workflow for understanding the basics of it.

I'm using the standard KSampler instead of the SamplerCustom node for ease of use for entry-level users.

CFG MUST be 1. 

You can experiment with samplers and schedulers.

Additional Relighting pipeline, it's here to show that the current limitations of Flux can be bypassed with traditional, existing 1.5 or SDXL pipelines if your hardware can handle loading more models.

This pipeline segments the subject, pastes it on top of the generated Flux image, and relights the image using IC-Light.

You can also use a CLIPTextEncodeFlux node, with separate Clip_l and t5xxl prompt fields and guidance already baked in, but I prefer using the standard text encode node and a separate FluxGuidance node.

The negative prompt field is left empty because at CFG 1, the CFG Flux wants, the negative prompt is discarded.

With XLabs' ControlNet, FluxGuidance MUST be 4.

XLabs' ControlNet starts acting wonky at strength>0.7, so beware.

In order to get the controlnet to work, you might want to change ComfyUI's branch to xlabs_flux_controlnet's branch by opening the ComfyUI dir in your terminal and typing:

git checkout xlabs_flux_controlnet

In this image to image workflow we're using the loaded image as both the controlnet reference and the size reference for the empty latent image.

If you get an error at the KSampler, it's because the size is not correct for Flux, since it has very specific needs (like SD3) in terms of Width and Height.

Change the side_length param to another value, like 1024, 1280 or whatever to make it work.

For square images it's easy (1024 works every time), for non-square images it's harder.

You might want to resize your image to a size that Flux accepts before loading it.

Workflow for this video: https://youtu.be/lgFxqG8eam4

If you want to see a Flux deep dive, watch it.

Download and place the dev FP16 version of Flux in the /models/unet folder:
https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-dev/blob/main/flux1-dev.safetensors

Download and place the VAE in the VAE folder:
https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-dev/tree/main/vae

Download and place the text encoder models (clip_l and either t5xxl fp8 or both fp8 and 16) in the /models/clip folder:
https://huggingface.co/comfyanonymous/flux_text_encoders/tree/main

If you run out of memory, under Load Diffusion Model's weight_dtype, select fp8_e4m3fn

If you run out of memory, under DualCLIPLoader select the t5xxl_fp8 model

The LORA can be bypassed if you don't care about the realism LORA.
